post_text:
Parents and Guardians,

If your student is absent due to illness, you must contact the office at 219-474-5167 by 9:00 am to report the absence and the reason for the absence. Students who are ill with a symptom consistent with COVID-19 will need to provide medical documentation of an alternative diagnosis or documentation of a negative COVID-19 test before being cleared to return to school. This documentation must be brought to the office prior to the student's return to school. Without this documentation, your student will need to remain home for ten days and be symptom/fever free for 24 hours before returning to school. Students may only join class remotely after the office has been notified of the absence and they are quarantined or out due to the ten day window, students cannot just choose to join remotely. We are very fortunate to be able to offer this option of remote learning in these situations in order for our students to stay current with their coursework.

Thank you,
Mr. Smith

SN Middle
September 4 at 5:02 PM ¬∑

Educational technology and its funding change daily. To keep up with these changes and their accompanying expenses, our school is participating in Murphy's Food King's Apples for the Students Program. The Apples for the Students Program enables our school to earn computers and iPads, sporting goods, audio visual equipment, and science supplies, with choices from hundreds of other awards, too! And, they‚Äôre all free! To earn these FREE awards we simply have to collect as many register receipts as possible from September 1st, 2020, through March 1st, 2021. Ask your friends and relatives to shop at Murphy's and save every receipt and deposit in the box for South Newton located by the exit door. You may also send the receipts to school with your student as often as possible. The school will count the value of the register tapes collected and redeem them for great educational awards that benefit your child. Thank you in advance for your participation!

South Newton Food Services
August 25 at 1:30 PM ¬∑

Welcome to September :)
I just want to thank parents and students personally for their understanding about the cold grab n go lunches(rebel meal) for the month of August. The administration team all come together and agreed that in these uncertain times and with reopening school very cautiously, and with all the changes that we would start the year this way.
The students have been great about keeping socially apart and dealing with the changes in a positive way.
With all that being said, we will still have limited choices and everything will be in closed containers but we will again be having hot lunches starting in September with the second option being the cold rebel meal. Thank you again!!

August 8 at 2:23 AM ¬∑

Our new 6th grade, the class of 2027, should check their school email for a Google form that will allow them to ask questions about starting 6th grade. These questions will be addressed in a live Zoom session scheduled to start at 6:00 p.m. on Tuesday, August 11. This session will not be interactive, so it will be important for us to receive your questions so we can address them. Details regarding the session and the ways you may access it will be forthcoming. Parents, feel free to sneak a question of your own onto your student's Google form.

August 6 at 3:14 PM ¬∑

Sadly, our annual Back to School Night has been cancelled. However, we realize that the first day of middle school can be very tense for our new 6th grade students. So as not to conflict with elementary back to school video conferences, on Tuesday, August 11, at 6:00 p.m., the 6th grade team will be hosting an optional panel discussion via Zoom to introduce themselves, discuss 6th grade, and answer questions. All 6th grade students should be checking their email later this week for a brief survey that will allow them to list their most pressing questions because we hope to answer them!

post_text:
Dear South Newton Family,

Attached is the South Newton School Corporation 2020-2021 Re-Entry Plan. The Plan will answer many questions you might have about bringing our staff and students back to school safely. As you will see, the first page of the Plan mentions how fluid the Coronavirus situation is, as well as our school being required to follow mandated guidelines set forth by state or federal governments. This plan was finalized last week, then voted on by the South Newton Board of Trustees last evening. Between the time of the Plan being finalized and voted on, Governor Holcomb has mandated facemasks for the state of Indiana. This mandate includes inside school buildings, specifically for students in grades three and higher. The mandate also includes all adults in school buildings. While the South Newton plan ‚Äúrecommends‚Äù the use of facemasks, until further notice, we will require facemasks (for grades three and higher) until the Governor‚Äôs mandate is lifted.

Sincerely,
Mr. Hall

https://www.newton.k12.in.us/images/20-21/re-entryplan2020-2021.pdf

July 14 at 12:37 PM ¬∑

UPDATE: We have become aware that locker numbers and schedules are not available on Harmony. Mrs. Miller can look them up for you when you arrive. Our apologies for this miscommunication.
Locker clean out starts today at 8:30. Remember the following:
1. Only one adult may accompany the middle school student(s) coming to clean out lockers.
2. No trash cans will be available.
3. You can bring your own bag or you may use a trash bag that we will provide.
4. All contents are to go into the bag so that you may sort through the contents at home.
5. Masks are optional, but social distancing is mandatory.

Thank you for observing and respecting these guidelines.

post_text:
Graduation guideline update:
Due to the fact that Governor Holcomb did not move the state to stage 5, there are some guidelines we need to follow to have graduation safely.

** Please try to limit the number of family and guests that are attending. Please follow the CDC Guidelines for all Hoosiers.
**Please maintain a social distance of 6 feet per family
** We strongly recommend face coverings to protect others and yourself
**Use precautions, Be respectful of others and Be Safe
**After graduation please return to your vehicles as quickly as possible and go enjoy this honorable day away from school
**We may indeed be dismissing parents and relatives by rows after graduation

The weather will be very hot. There are no water fountains available at school. You might want to bring your own water. We will be providing water to all graduates and staff members. Restrooms will be available.
Thank you for your cooperation on all the above requests. This will hopefully keep the Rebel Family safe.
Mr. Huckstep

Our hearts were full today. From dawn to dusk we planned, strategized, created, decorated, anticipated, reacted, swelled with pride, smiled and laughed, yelled loudly, encouraged and praised, cried and wished. We love you. No way around it. We would bend over backwards to see you succeed and prosper. This spring has been a crazy time but we will overcome together and persevere. We can‚Äôt fathom what creations will develop because of this time but are excited to start that adventure with you this fall, whatever it may look like. Your Art Department, K-12, is chomping at the bit to explore this adventure with you. Have an excellent summer and never stop creating to discover who you are!

post_text: K-12 Teacher Parade - ROUTE MAP ADDED from Brook to Goodland. Friday May 22nd. We will start in Brook at 2:00pm, hopefully get to Goodland around 2:45, then to Kentland around 3:30.
text: K-12 Teacher Parade - ROUTE MAP ADDED from Brook to Goodland. Friday May 22nd. We will start in Brook at 2:00pm, hopefully get to Goodland around 2:45, then to Kentland around 3:30.

post_text: Who misses their teachers? Who misses their students? Who misses their friends? Who misses all our staff? Who misses school??? Well, we all sure do which is why we are throwing ALL OUR STUDENTS K-12 A PARADEüç¨üéâ Teachers, staff & administrators will be throwing a parade through Brook, Goodland & Kentland on Friday May 22nd. We will start in Brook at 2:00pm, hopefully get to Goodland around 2:45, then to Kentland around 3:30. Pictures of the route are provided. We do ask that you maintain social distancing during the parade and respect those guidelines set forth by the CDC üòÉ HEY SENIORS, it would be AMAZING if you wore your cap to the parade üéì We are SO EXCITED to see our students & parents...hope to see you there!!!!! SPECIAL THANKS to all who helped plan the routes, the Fire Departments in each town & our local police departments. We love where we live & are so thankful for you all!
text: Who misses their teachers? Who misses their students? Who misses their friends? Who misses all our staff? Who misses school??? Well, we all sure do which is why we are throwing ALL OUR STUDENTS K-12 A PARADEüç¨üéâ Teachers, staff & administrators will be throwing a parade through Brook, Goodland & Kentland on Friday May 22nd. We will start in Brook at 2:00pm, hopefully get to Goodland around 2:45, then to Kentland around 3:30. Pictures of the route are provided. We do ask that you maintain social distancing during the parade and respect those guidelines set forth by the CDC üòÉ HEY SENIORS, it would be AMAZING if you wore your cap to the parade üéì We are SO EXCITED to see our students & parents...hope to see you there!!!!! SPECIAL THANKS to all who helped plan the routes, the Fire Departments in each town & our local police departments. We love where we live & are so thankful for you all!

I have attached information about athletics for this coming fall. You will see that last year's physical will be recognized, with some exceptions. You will also find a link to Family ID. The IHSAA has stated that there are no waivers to the eligibility rules, all students must meet academic requirements to participate.

I hope to see everyone back in the building in the fall. Stay safe.

post_text:
Message from Mr. Bell

Hello Everyone,
I hope everyone is home, safe and healthy. As many of you know, the IHSAA has cancelled the remainder of the spring season. Summer schedules and practices are also on hold until we get further direction from the state. As soon as we know what & when we can start summer activities we will let you know.

I have had questions about the sports physicals. Right now we have these on hold until we are allowed to gather back in the school. Currently there are no plans for the physicals until July or August.

Lastly all of those who made contact with their spring coach and signed up will be given a varsity letter for this spring.

Have a Happy Easter, stay safe and healthy. CAN'T WAIT TO SEE EVERYONE IN THE BUILDING!!

POUR HOUSE Bar & Grill
March 15 at 6:31 PM ¬∑

*Jasper & Newton County Families*

With recent events and schools being closed, we want to help. We know theres families whos kids eat breakfast and lunch at school ( I know this 1st hand as our child is one..and I had to go "shopping" for those extra meals just recently), not everyone is able to right off the bat with the extreme and sudden decision that was made. So we're going to try and help, if for some reason your child needs lunch we will offer a personal pizza (or other size depending on how many kiddos) for free. We're checking in with our vendors for other options ie hotdogs etc. We ask that this gesture isnt abused and only for the families in need so someone in need isnt going without or deplete our resources (we're a mom and pop place not big corporate). These orders will have to be for "togo" as we're a 21+ establishment. Our plan is to do this until school is back in session or a forced closure. Please be kind and patient with one another we're all in this together üíô

Phone: 219-345-7687

FOOD PANTRY UPDATE:
It is with a heavy heart that I have to announce that out of growing concern for the health and safety of all involved, the Food Pantry in Kentland, Indiana, is suspending operation until further notice. If you find yourself in a dire food emergency, message the Covenant Federated Church Facebook page or leave a message on the church's answering machine. We apologise for any inconveniences this may cause but feel this is the best decision to keep everyone involved, patrons and volunteers alike, safe and healthy.

*Please help spread the word by sharing this post

January 27 at 2:56 PM ¬∑

The South Newton wrestling team finished second in the MWC 4 points behind North Newton Saturday. SN had two conference champions, Blake Whaley at 120 and Dane Smith at 170. Dane also secured his 100th career victory Saturday. Other strong performances were given by Kane Sell at 126 and Domminic Sanders at 285 both coming in second. Ty Hoaks, Lane Deal, Gage Ely, Daniel Tordai and Will Balenseifer all placed 3rd. This finished a strong regular season for the wrestling team, with an overall record of 15-13. The wrestling team will next see action Saturday February 1st when they travel to Twin Lakes for Sectional.
